        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">if you are in melee range of the mob you are fighting, you are too close :)<BR>i always fight from pretty far back, darkness pull from max range, send pet, fear, DoT, med and just keep feared.<BR>only mobs you should be in melee range for are those that you can't hit with spells unless you are there...</P><P>which reminds me, has anyone tried doing that to the uber mobs that resist everything we throw at them?</P><P><marquee><b><font=red> ABILLISTER "MONKEY" ABU-Povar</font></b></marquee><BR><marquee><a href="<a href="http://whiteangels.guildsofeq.com/MainFrame.asp" target="_blank">http://whiteangels.guildsofeq.com/MainFrame.asp</a>">Sojourn's Talon</a></marquee><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
